<component type="desktop-application">
  <id>io.github.averyvisentin.TerminalTetris</id>

  <name>Terminal Tetris</name>
  <summary>A feature-rich terminal-based Tetris game written in Python.</summary>

  <metadata_license>MIT</metadata_license>
  <project_license>MIT</project_license>

  <description>
    <p>
      This is a terminal-based Tetris game written in Python. It aims to be a feature-rich implementation of the classic game with modern mechanics.
    </p>
    <ul>
      <li>Classic Tetris Gameplay</li>
      <li>Multiple Gamemodes: Marathon, Sprint, and Timed</li>
      <li>Modern Mechanics: T-Spin detection and a back-to-back bonus system</li>
      <li>Save State Feature</li>
      <li>Hold Functionality</li>
      <li>Persistent High Scores and Settings</li>
      <li>Customizable Controls and Gameplay</li>
    </ul>
  </description>

